headline: Bank earnings, United earnings, PPI, Fed talk: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime with Josh Lipton outlines the top stories for investors to watch on Wednesday, July 16. A fresh slate of earnings reports is set to be published. In the morning, Bank of America (BAC), Morgan Stanley (MS), Goldman Sachs (GS), ASML (ASML), and Johnson & Johnson (JNJ) will release earnings. In the afternoon, United Airlines (UAL) will report earnings. Producer Price Index (PPI) data for June will be out in the morning, with economists expecting a slight uptick on a month-over-month basis. More commentary from Federal Reserve officials is coming, with remarks from Fed governor Michael Barr and New York Fed President John Williams. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here.
